entries.journal_entry_completion_summary: You finally gotten to Jabba. Jabba sent you to EV-9D9, his torture droid in the bowles of his palace. EV-9D9 has the head but wants you to help her first.
entries.journal_entry_description: According to Watto, the droid's head was last seen at Jabba's Palace. You're probably going to need to grease all the palms leading to Jabba before you actually get to meet Jabba.
entries.task00_journal_entry_description: Watto says that Jabba was the last one who owned the droid before it was disassembled. Perhaps he knows where the head is. In order to be granted a personal audience with Jabba to speak with him, you'll need to earn the right to that honor. Speak with Reelo Baruk just inside of Jabba's Palace, and he'll be able to help you get started.
entries.task01_journal_entry_description: Jabba's torture droid, EV-9D9, was given the droid for disassembly. Maybe she knows where the head is.
